 look into the history of psychological trauma. In addition, it engages with current disability, pensions, and compensation issues that remain hotly contested and reflects on the power of commemoration in the healing process.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aKorean War, 1950-1953xMedical care. 0aKorean War, 1950-1953xPsychological aspects. 0aMilitary psychiatryzCommonwealth countriesxHistoryy20th century. 0aPsychic traumazCommonwealth countriesxHistoryy20th century. 0aSoldiersxMental health serviceszCommonwealth countriesxHistoryy20th century. 0aSoldiersxMental healthzCommonwealth countriesxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Military / Korean War.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311127365508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017z978311127619908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311141793640uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077483480340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774834803423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774834803/original  a978-3-11-127365-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-127619-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-141793-6  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles